 The body of Christ has been urged to wake up from its slumber and take its rightful place in advancing God’s kingdom on earth in all good works. Pastor-in-charge of Delta Province 2 of The Redeemed Christian Church of God (RCCG), Pastor Ezekiel Olukahunsi, made the call at the headquarters, Shekinah Mega Parish, along NPA road, Edjeba, Warri, Delta State. He urged Christians to embrace the virtue of making others happy on a daily basis because of the law of harvest. Akinadewo appeals to OAIC leaders to  embrace monogamy Kogi gov election: CAN calls for prayers Adefarasin hosts Travis Greene, Sinach, Todd Dulaney, others… Don’t commercialise God’s grace,  Adegboye tells clerics “God remembered Israel because of Abraham. Your good waits for you in the future. “What have you done that will make your children suffer in future? God can, because of you alone, break protocols,” he said. Olukahunsi, while speaking on the theme: “Remember Me oh Lord,” reiterated that “every good or evil deed has a reward. No good goes unnoticed. What should God remember you for?” According to him, “When it’s my time, no power can stop it. Every man in life has a day of remembrance waiting for him.” The former police officer, who got a call from God to go into full time ministry in the 80s, urged Nigerians, especially Christians, to keep seeking God’s face for themselves, their families and Nigeria and always engage in good works for God to put them into remembrance. SHOCKING LIFE STORY!!! Abuja Man reveals (FREE) secret Fruits that Increased his Manh0d size and Lasting Power in just 7days… CLICK HERE
